      As a result, she was arrested and jailed on numerous occasions. In January 1944, Kasturba Ji suffered two heart attacks after which she was confined to her bed much of the time.       About

      Description

      Kasturba Mohandas Gandhi was an Indian political activist who was involved in the Indian independence movement during British India. She was married to Mohandas Karamchand Gandhi, commonly known as Mahatma Gandhi. Wikipedia
      Born: April 11, 1869, Porbandar, India
      Died: February 22, 1944 (age 74 years), Pune, India
      Children: Harilal Gandhi, Devdas Gandhi, Ramdas Gandhi, Manilal Gandhi
      Great grandchildren: Leela Gandhi, Kirti Menon, Amrita Gandhi, MORE
      Spouse: Mahatma Gandhi (m. 18831944)
      Grandchildren: Arun Manilal Gandhi, Gopalkrishna Gandhi, MORE
      Parents: Gokuladas Kapadia, Vrajkunwerba Kapadia
